A binomial trial was then used to determine whether or not the replacement animal was PI. If the replacement animal was not PI, it was then assigned a random age of seroconversion (Agesero) sampled from an exponential distribution with a half-life of 1095 days (Equation 2) to reflect the average age of seroconversion in the general population of cattle [35,49,50]. The purpose was to account for the increasing probability that older cattle will have been previously exposed to BVDV either through natural infection or immunization.2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
